items.title: Rhinotia spp.
items.content_text: There were type types of Rhinotia sp. weevils around this morning. The ones with white markings on their back I think are Rhinotia hemisticta. The plain ones, like this, to my eyes seem to have slightly 'fatter' front legs, although they may also be Rhinotia hemisticta. I don't know if this variablility is within the same species or denotes a different species.

items.title: Rhinotia spp.
items.content_text: Quite a few of these around this morning, at least 20 seen around the place. Looks like Rhinotia hemisticta to me, but not certain.
